==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Lye
<hw>Lye</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <altsp>[Written also
<asp>lie</asp> and <asp>ley</asp>.]</altsp> <ety>[AS.
<ets>le⟦aacute⟧h</ets>; akin to D. <ets>loog</ets>, OHG.
<ets>louga</ets>, G. <ets>lauge</ets>; cf. Icel. <ets>laug</ets> a bath,
a hot spring.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A strong caustic alkaline solution
of potassium salts, obtained by leaching wood ashes. It is much used in
making soap, etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>Sodium hydroxide or potassium
hydroxide, or a concentrated aqueous solution of either
compound.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Lye</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Lye
<hw>Lye</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Railroad)</fld> <def>A short side
line, connected with the main line; a turn-out; a siding.</def>
<mark>[Eng.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Lye</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Lye
<hw>Lye</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A falsehood.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<see>See <er>Lie</er>.</see>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Lyencephala</ent>⟦br⟧
